OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776985387
OL,3,CLewis Moody 'takes the baton' from
OL,4,CDoddie Weir and Rob Burrow in MND fight
OL,6,FFormer England captain Lewis Moody
OL,7,Fwill use every lesson rugby taught him
OL,8,Fto confront his recent diagnosis of
OL,9,FMotor Neurone Disease (MND).
OL,11,FAnnouncing a 500-mile fundraising
OL,12,Fcycle ride, which Jonny Wilkinson and
OL,13,Fother former teammates have been
OL,14,Fpersuaded to take part in, he said he
OL,15,Fsees himself as a successor to Doddie
OL,16,FWeir and Rob Burrow in the fight
OL,17,Fagainst MND: "I feel that I am being
OL,18,Fbrought off the bench to take that
OL,19,Fbaton forward and try to get this job
OL,20,Fdone.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776985387
OL,3,CLewis Moody 'takes the baton' from
OL,4,CDoddie Weir and Rob Burrow in MND fight
OL,6,F"Maybe it should be 'ball', but baton
OL,7,Ffeels like the right analogy. Call it
OL,8,Fa privilege. In some ways, I have
OL,9,Ffound it a privilege."
OL,11,FThe bike route visits all Moody's
OL,12,Fformer clubs and ends up at
OL,13,FTwickenham, where he will deliver the
OL,14,Fball on the day of the Gallagher
OL,15,FPremiership final.
OL,26,@qD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776985387
OL,3,CLewis Moody 'takes the baton' from
OL,4,CDoddie Weir and Rob Burrow in MND fight
OL,6,F"I suppose from a personal point of
OL,7,Fview, there is something about wanting
OL,8,Fto show that I can still do things
OL,9,Flike this. It is not about winning the
OL,10,Frace or anything, it's about getting
OL,11,Fto an end."
OL,13,FBut as he launched the challenge,
OL,14,FMoody was honest about how the disease
OL,15,Fis already impacting how he lives his
OL,16,Flife.
OL,18,F"The hardest thing is noticing little
OL,19,Fthings every day. The other day I
OL,20,Fnoticed a slight difference in my
OL,21,Ffinger strength," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776985387
OL,3,CLewis Moody 'takes the baton' from
OL,4,CDoddie Weir and Rob Burrow in MND fight
OL,6,F"Whether it was opening a bottle top,
OL,7,Fholding a fork, or cutting your food.
OL,9,F"Those little things, mentally, are a
OL,10,Fchallenge when they present
OL,11,Fthemselves. At the minute, touch wood,
OL,12,Feverything still remains slow, so
OL,13,Fhopefully it will continue."
OL,15,FJoining Moody and Wilkinson will be
OL,16,Fother heroes of England's 2003 World
OL,17,FCup win, including Mike Tindall, Phil
OL,18,FVickery and Ben Kay ` many of whom
OL,19,Fhave never even been on a bike.
OL,26,@uD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
